  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "The rank you achieve in the MU-OET (Manipal University Online Entrance Test) will depend on the overall score distribution of all candidates who took the exam, as well as the total number of candidates. A score of 132 out of 200 could place you at various ranks depending on how others performed.\n\nTo get an accurate estimate of your rank, you will need to compare your score with the previous years' ranking trend for the same exam or consult the official resources released by Manipal University after the exam results are published. They usually provide ranks along with the cutoff scores for various programs.\n\nFor a more precise prediction, you may also want to reach out to current students, academic forums, or coaching centers that focus on these entrance exams.",
